    "The scene continues toward the boatyard."
    # [Scene: The Boatyard | During the stormhead]
    hide noah_reyes

    scene bg ch12_735866_7 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Wood snapping; shouted coordinates; the Beacon's lights strobes a frantic Morse]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Percussion at a fever pitch; brass slashes]
    "You run like an animal between tasks — from the pump controls to the hand-lines, from the reed mat fortification to the tow of an upturned dinghy. Your boots slip. Your jacket is heavy with water"
    "and with the ache of decisions made under pressure. You are both leader and laborer; you locate seams and sew them with hands that have known hard things."
    show eli_duarte at left:
        zoom 0.7

    eli_duarte "You doing okay? You look like you could break."
    "A laugh that is not a laugh catches in your throat. You do not answer with an easy affirmation. You answer the only way you can."
    show asha_moreno at right:
        zoom 0.7

    asha_moreno "I am doing what must be done."
    "Eli studies you as if trying to remember a map he once learned by heart. His eyes are wet with rain, or with something that could be anger, or grief — you can't tell."

    eli_duarte "Good. Then don't go breaking on us."
    "He returns to a group hauling a soaked beam. You go back to the line, heart hammering, mind a wire that cannot stay still."
    # [Scene: Near the Beacon — the storm's eye is passing]
    hide eli_duarte
    hide asha_moreno

    scene bg ch12_735866_8 at full_bg
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: The alarm's tempo shifts — high, then lower, then an angular silence]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single low sustained cello note under brittle percussion]
    "For a breathless minute the storm seems to relent. The sea's voice drops as if listening. People check each other's faces like lifelines."
    "Lila Park approaches you again. Her voice is quieter now. The clinical edge has thinned, or perhaps you are simply more raw and forgiving than you were at the start of the night."
    show lila_park at left:
        zoom 0.7

    lila_park "Your oversight was... effective. The team adapted to your chain of command faster than expected."

    "You want to say something that would make her look at the town not as a model but as a heart. Instead you find yourself saying what you must" "The town answers to itself first. Any help that undermines that is not help."
    "Lila's face is a study in careful neutrality. She presses her lips together, a small seam."

    lila_park "We all misread what 'help' looks like sometimes."
    "She turns away, the words like a little stone thrown into deep, dark water. You cannot see the ripple she felt or meant. Her reaction remains unreadable — careful, measured, as if she is cataloguing the human variables for a later pitch."
    "Noah stands close, his shoulder brushing yours. There is no easy line to draw between exhaustion and intimacy tonight. The two of you have been in the same worn trench. You have bled the same salt."
    show noah_reyes at right:
        zoom 0.7

    noah_reyes "You kept your end. You kept us."
    "You want to answer with something that would promise forever. The truth — harder and truer — comes out instead."
    show asha_moreno at center:
        zoom 0.7

    asha_moreno "I kept what I could. We lost things. We'll have to live with that."
    "Noah's hand finds yours and holds it. The gesture is small and steady and weighty. It says: not perfect, but together."

    noah_reyes "Then let's start from there."
    "His voice shakes. Yours does too, though you try to hide it in the noise of the last pumps cooling. There is no tidy answer. There is only the knot of trust made in exhaustion and shared risk."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Wind downshifts into a thin, tremulous hiss; then, a long, hollow silence like lungs emptied]
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A single minor chord struck and left to ring; then nothing]
    "Dawn doesn't feel like a resolve. It feels like an inventory. Lantern glow as the first tally light. Hands numb and faces stung by salt. The town is raw: some porches are gone, some foundations washed"
    "to tooth; the market survived with wet awnings; a lane of investor housing — bright and new last week — is a memory floating somewhere beyond the next headland."
    "You walk the Promenade, the boards underfoot sticky with silt. People gather in clusters, touching what remains as if to test whether it will be taken again. They look at you and at Noah and at"
    "each other with a hunger that is not anger only. It is grief wrapped in relief."
    "Marta finds you and collapses her forehead against your shoulder for a long second that contains more than words. When she pulls away she is all bark again, but softer at the edges."
    hide lila_park
    show marta_chen at left:
        zoom 0.7

    marta_chen "We did what we had to. We lost things but no one went out to sea alone."
    "You nod. You want to say the right words: that you are sorry for what was lost, that you are proud of what was saved. None of those will restore wood or paint or the hulls of small lives. They are small sutures on a wide wound."
    "You feel an ember of fierce integrity smoldering in your chest. You and the town chose a path that felt right even as the sea punished it. That choice did not guarantee victory. It guaranteed honesty."
    "It cost you sleep, property, future promises carved into contract language. It saved people. The balance sheet is messy and human."
    "Noah stands at your side, his hand still finding yours in the small, cheating quiet. When he speaks it is a low thing, meant only for you."

    noah_reyes "There won't be easy promises now. There will be hard work and honest reckoning. Are you with me for that?"
    "You look at the town — at Eli sanding a splintered plank, at Lila's crew packing equipment into crates, at a child counting the survivors with solemn, small fingers. Your answer lodges like a stone, heavy, certain."

    asha_moreno "Yes. For as long as it takes."
    "There is no fanfare. No sudden peace. Just a pressed hand and the smell of salt and wet wood and a sky that will not forget what it has done."
    hide noah_reyes
    hide asha_moreno
    hide marta_chen

    scene bg ch12_735866_9 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: A soft, unresolved chord that hangs in the damp air]
    "The sea took what it would this night. It taught you that some losses cannot be negotiated away, only mourned and then reclaimed in the work of living. What remains is a promise that will have"
    "to be rewritten every morning: who we are when the lights go out, how we hold each other, and which parts of our town remain common ground."

